ance.', '水银是流体状之。'), (8561, 'Mercury weighs more than water by about 14 times.', '水银比水重约十三倍。'), (8562, 'Mercury is too dry and poor in oxygen.', '水星上面过于干燥，并且缺乏氧气。'), (8563, 'He has no mercury in him.', '他没有精神。'), (8564, 'Mercy to the enemies means cruelty to the people.', '对敌人的仁慈就意味着对人民的残忍。'), (8565, 'They showed their enemies no mercy.', '他们不给敌人半点仁慈。'), (8566, 'They never appealed to us for mercy.', '他们从不向我们乞求怜悯。'), (8567, 'The commander showed mercy to the prisoners of war.', '司令官对战俘十分怜悯。'), (8568, 'The prisoner implored the king for mercy.', '囚犯恳求国王开恩。'), (8569, 'The prisoner appealed to the judge for mercy.', '囚犯恳求法官开恩。'), (8570, 'The king showed no mercy and killed all the prisoners.', '这个国王没有宽容之心，杀死了所有的犯人。'), (8571, 'Don\'t scold him, he is a mere child.,', '责备他,他只不过是个孩子。'), (8572, 'Her liberal views were soon revealed as mere posturing.', '她那些开明的观点很快地就暴露出只不过是做做样子而已。'), (8573, 'The peasant laboured for a mere pittance.', '农民仅仅是为了微不足道的收入而辛苦地劳作。'), (8574, 'A mere child cannot do the work of a man.', '仅仅是个孩子是不能做成人工作的。'), (8575, 'The mere quotation outtells all commentary.', '纯粹的引用文句比所有一手注解更能表达。'), (8576, 'They are not merely content to fill the stomach.', '他们不仅仅满足于填饱肚子。'), (8577, 'I accepted this job merely for the high salary.', '我仅仅是因为高薪才接受了这份工作。'), (8578, 'She is merely a child.', '她只不过是个孩子。'), (8579, 'I merely suggest you should do it again.', '我只是建议你重新做这件事。'), (8580, 'This method at least had the merit of simplicity.', '这种办法至少有简单明了的优点。'), (8581, 'Charms strikes the sight, but merit wins the soul.,', '貌吸引目光,优点赢得心灵。'), (8582, 'That will subtract nothing from his merit.', '那将无损于他的功绩。'), (8583, 'Promotion should be based on merit alone.', '晋升应完全根据功绩。'), (8584, 'I want to get the job on merit.', '我要凭才能得到这份工作。'), (8585, 'This is a proposal of some merit.', '这是个有价值的建议。'), (8586, 'There is a merry smile on her face.', '她脸上露出愉快的微笑。'), (8587, 'He is in a very merry mood today.', '他今天心情极为愉快。'), (8588, 'Merry Christmas!', '圣诞快乐！'), (8589, 'He ended his speech with a mer