 her hair.', '她头发上戴着黄色缎带。'), (12155, 'Ribbon hung from the bride\'s bouquet was tied in a bow.', '从新娘的花束上垂下来的丝带打成了一个结。'), (12156, 'I had to change the typewriter ribbon.', '我不得不换掉打字机的色带。'), (12157, 'We will be glad to get rid of him.', '摆脱他，我们将很高兴。'), (12158, 'You must rid yourself of this melancholy mood.', '你一定要摆脱这种忧愁情绪。'), (12159, 'We must try every way to rid ourselves of these debts.', '我们要想尽一切办法来摆脱这些债务。'), (12160, 'It is necessary to get rid of bureaucratic practices.', '必须清除官僚习气。'), (12161, 'Recurvature follows after it traverses the ridge axis.', '预料尼伯特将于横过副高脊线后开始转向。'), (12162, 'Riding on the ridge of the bridge, the proud bride shouts loudly to the cloud.', '骄傲的新娘骑在桥脊上对着云大声喊。'), (12163, 'He walked along the mountain ridge.', '他顺着山脊走。'), (12164, 'The evening before the battle, Wellington took up a defensive position along, and to the rear of, a long ridge.', '那场战斗的前夜，威灵顿沿一条长长的山脊背后占据了一个防守阵地。'), (12165, 'A gentle breeze from the Blue Ridge Mountains carried the scent of honeysuckle.', '从蓝岭山脉吹过来的和风，带来了忍冬花的芬芳。'), (12166, 'Instead Meldrum\'s visit to a ridge in the Blue Mountains set him firmly on a quest he has been on since.', '麦德伦跑去蓝山山脉一探究竟，没想到就此加入追寻答案的行列。'), (12167, 'His social pretensions make him appear ridiculous.', '他冒充上流社会人士而出尽洋相。'), (12168, 'His aristocratic manners seemed ridiculous in this poor area.', '在这个贫穷的地区，他的贵族气派显得很可笑。'), (12169, 'I\'ll show you how to settle such ridiculous stuff.', '你瞧我怎样来对付这种无稽之谈。'), (12170, 'That\'s ridiculous.', '那太荒唐了。'), (12171, 'That fat woman looked ridiculous in her tight golden dress.', '那位胖妇人穿着金色的紧身礼服，显得滑稽可笑。'), (12172, 'Rifle reports could be heard in the distance.', '听得见远处传来的步枪声。'), (12173, 'He accidentally triggered his rifle.', '他无意中扣发了他步枪的扳机。'), (12174, 'The tent has a rigid support.', '帐篷有一个坚硬的支柱。'), (12175, 'He is a man of very rigid principles.', '他是一个原则性很强的人。'), (12176, 'He\'s very rigid in his ideas.', '他的想法非常固执。'), (12177, 'She was rigid with fear.', '她害怕得全身僵住了。'), (12178, 'It\'s an exercise which adds a touch of the comic opera to his rigid training routines.', '这一练习给他那刻板的训练程序平添了一份滑稽的色彩。'), (12179, 'The branches were weighed down with ripe apples.', '苹果成熟了把树枝都压弯了。'), (12180, 'Most tomatoes are red when ripe, but some kinds are yellow.', '大多数西红柿成熟时是红色的，但有些品种是黄色的。'), (12181, 'The ripe apples picked easily..', '熟的苹果易于采摘.'), (12182, 'The time was ripe for a challenge to the power of the government.', '时机已经成熟，可以向政府权力提出挑战了。'), (12183, 'These apples are not ripe; they are sour.', '这些苹果不熟，是酸的。'), (12184, 'I picked a ripe apple from the tree.', '我从树上摘下一只熟的苹果。'), (12185, 'It was mid-summer when the crops were ripe.', '庄稼熟的时候已是仲夏。'), (12186, 'He saved my life at the risk of his own.', '他冒着自己的生命危险救了我的命。'), (12187, 'Investors in Central Asia have to face political risk.,', '中亚,投资者还得面临政治风险。'), (12188, 'Loans to farmers are now considered to be a bad risk.', '贷款给农民现在被认为要承受糟糕的投资报酬风险。'), (12189, 'He is hound out of his job by jealous rival.', '他受到忌妒他的竞争者的算计而被迫离职。'), (12190, 'The party leader has been supplanted by his rival.', '那位政党领导已被他的对手取而代之了。'), (12191, 'He could only roar in a gruff voice.', '他仅能以沙哑的声音吼叫着。'), (12192, 'In the picture, the dragons and tigers won\'t roar.,', '画里,龙不吟虎不啸（小小书僮可笑可笑）。'), (12193, 'We roar all like bears, and mourn sore like doves: we look for judgment, but there is none; for salvation, but it is far off from us.', '我们咆哮如熊，哀呜如鸽。指望公平，却是没有。指望救恩，却远离我们。'), (12194, 'He roared with pain.', '他疼得大叫起来。'), (12195, 'Let\'s have a nice roast for Sunday dinner.', '我们星期天晚上好好吃一顿烤肉吧。'), (12196, 'His mouth watered at the sight of roast.', '他看见烤肉就垂涎三尺。'), (12197, 'They had a hot dog roast last Sunday.', '他们上星期天举行了一次烤热狗野餐会。'), (12198, 'The toy robot moved forward with quick jerky steps.', '玩具机器人一颠一颠地走得很快。'), (12199, 'Japanese industry is making increasing use of robots.', '日本工业越来越多地使用机器人。'), (12200, 'The robot is a marvel of modern engineering.', '机器人是现代工程技术的奇迹。'), (12201, 'They sent a distress rocket.', '他们发出了一枚呼救信号火箭。'), (12202, 'She served a fillet of chicken with a roc