n.', '人文精神的建立首先要靠人文教育。'), (16939, 'My laundry will not dry because of the humidity.', '由于湿度关系，我的衣物无法晾干。'), (16940, 'Humidity is a measure of moisture in the atmosphere.', '湿度是空气内含水分多少的量度。'), (16941, 'It\'s said by forecast that the humidity in the air today is 60%', '据预报说今天的空气湿度是百分之六十。'), (16942, 'Humidity caused me another fit of rheumatism.', '湿气使我的风湿病又发作了。'), (16943, 'It\'s the humidity that makes it so uncomfortable today.', '湿气使得今天很不舒服。'), (16944, 'The hunter hurled his spear at the tiger.', '猎人用力把他的长矛向虎投去。'), (16945, 'I\'ll hurl him out of the club if he dare tell the secret!', '如果他胆敢泄密，我就要把他赶出俱乐部。'), (16946, 'To hurl abuse is in no way to fight.', '谩骂决不是战斗。'), (16947, 'Businessmen will hurl their money about to get noticed.', '商人愿意挥霍钱财来引起注意。'), (16948, 'The best cure for unhappiness is to hurl yourself into your work.', '医治愁苦的最好办法就是全身心地投入工作。'), (16949, 'The hurricane destroyed the whole village.', '飓风把整个村子都毁掉了。'), (16950, 'The hurricane screamed outside.', '外面飓风呼啸著。'), (16951, 'The hurricane has a speed of 73 miles per hour.73', '每小时73英里。'), (16952, 'The radio alerted the citizens to prepare for the hurricane.', '电台警告市民们作好预防暴风准备。'), (16953, 'It was blowing gales of hurricane this time yesterday.', '昨天的这个时候正刮着狂风。'), (16954, 'The hypothesis promptly attracted some interest.', '这个假说很快引起了注意。'), (16955, 'The validity of the hypothesis can be tested.', '这种假说的可靠性是经得起考验的。'), (16956, 'His hypothesis turned out to be correct.', '事实证明他的假设是正确的。'), (16957, 'The survey result consisted with our hypothesis.', '调查结果和我们的假设相一致。'), (16958, 'Let me enumerate many flaws in your hypothesis.', '让我列举你前提中的许多谬误。'), (16959, 'No serious arguments that dispute this hypothesis have been advanced.', '对于这些前提，尚未发生激烈的争论。'), (16960, 'All this is mere hypothesis.', '所有的一切都仅仅是猜测。'), (16961, 'Janet became hysterical and began screaming.', '珍妮特变得歇斯底里，开始尖叫。'), (16962, 'His hysterical laughter made everybody stunned.', '他那歇斯底里的笑声使所有的人不知所措。'), (16963, 'He is hysterical at the sight of the photo.', '他